T*
(on your computer, which is bizarrely correlated to massive unexplained CPU usage in) Tj
T*
(WindowServer \(a system process\) [1] , and made my whole computer slow even when Chrome wasn?t) Tj
T*
(running . Deleting Chrome and Keystone made my computer way, way faster, all the time . Long) Tj
T*
(story: I noticed my brand new 16? MacBook Pro started acting sluggishly doing even trivial) Tj
T*
(things like scrolling. Activity Monitor showed nothing from Google using the CPU, but) Tj
T*
(WindowServer was taking ~80%, which is abnormally high \(it should use Doing all the normal) Tj
T*
(things \(quitting apps, logging out other users, restarting, zapping PRAM/SMC, etc\) did nothing,) Tj
T*
(then I remembered I had installed Chrome a while back to test a website. I deleted Chrome, and) Tj
T*
(noticed Keystone while deleting some of Chrome?s other preferences and caches. I deleted) Tj
T*
(everything from Google I could find, restarted the computer, and it was like night-and-day.) Tj
